{"type":"message","id":"43b1e764","parentId":"9a5c3838","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:16:16.690Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Update de 5 min:\n\n- **Step exacto actual:** ainda **`S1 / scene_director batch-level`**, antes de qualquer `b1_step1_*`\n- **Concluído até agora:**\n  - PM ✅\n  - VO bootstrap ✅\n  - VO `script_ready` ✅\n  - S1 arrancou ✅\n  - `scene_director` gerou inputs `sd_001`…`sd_005` ✅\n  - `scene_director` gerou outputs `sd_001_output.json`…`sd_005_output.json` ✅\n\n- **Estado actual:**\n  - continua **sem novos checkpoints**\n  - continua **sem `b1_step1_screenplay`**\n  - continua **sem `b1_step2_screenplay_validated`**\n  - continua **sem sinais de `tts_polish`**\n  - portanto o bloqueio continua a parecer estar **entre o fim dos batches do `scene_director` e o merge/validator do screenplay**\n\n- **Leitura honesta:**\n  - não houve progresso observável nos últimos **10 minutos**\n  - o run não está bloqueado em PM nem VO\n  - está **estagnado dentro do S1, antes do primeiro checkpoint `b1_*`**\n\n- **Próximo checkpoint esperado:**\n  - `b1_step1_screenplay`\n  - depois `b1_step2_screenplay_validated`\n  - só depois entrada no `tts_polish`\n\nSe isto se mantiver no próximo reminder, o diagnóstico operacional já fica bem claro: **o choke point real deste run está no handoff pós-`scene_director`, não no batch generation em si**.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce17b6032c81908ca3afefe9ded678\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1402,"output":361,"cacheRead":28928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30691,"cost":{"input":0.0035050000000000003,"output":0.0054150000000000005,"cacheRead":0.007232,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016152}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775114144855,"responseId":"resp_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce17a2f0f88190acb2b0e8c7de1a68"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6728ba46","parentId":"43b1e764","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:20:20.216Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:3ee6e17f-87b0-4e46-8b2c-c4baff05ce72 s1-overnight-supervision] Continue overnight supervision of S1 robustness work. Read the current workspace context and recent memory. Prioritize either making S1 robust enough to progress materially toward b1_complete or producing a strong technical verdict on whether the current OpenClaw path for S1 should be kept, redesigned, or aborted. Check current run state, inspect latest failures, continue the highest-leverage fix, update TASKS.md / memory/2026-04-01.md if important conclusions emerge, and send a concise progress summary to the current session.\nCurrent time: Thursday, April 2nd, 2026 — 04:20 (America/Sao_Paulo) / 2026-04-02 07:20 UTC\n\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself."}],"timestamp":1775114420134}}
