IY|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce191725648190b68031396996f701","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\CONTEXT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\CONTEXT.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1215,"output":153,"cacheRead":46208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47576,"cost":{"input":0.0030375000000000003,"output":0.002295,"cacheRead":0.011552,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0168845}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775114513483,"responseId":"resp_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce19132e748190804ebf2f83e91fa8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ea978f9","parentId":"8a31d455","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:21:58.955Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_K3Duglxppr4c7bqnwgVmUq6z|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce19172548819082421422c21fe8e5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# STATE.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector state model\nThe supervisor should reason about states such as:\n- `not_started`\n- `running`\n- `retrying`\n- `blocked`\n- `complete`\n- `failed`\n\n## Authority rule\nState transitions belong to the supervisor.\nOperators and deterministic components may emit results, but they do not own sector state sovereignty.\n\n## Retry policy (v1)\n- structural preflight failures -> fail fast\n- operator execution failures -> retry batch or step depending on mapping\n- scene_director batch failures that are mechanically recoverable -> prefer deterministic reconstruction/canonicalization first\n- scene_director batch structural/fidelity failures that remain after recovery -> retry via `retry_planner`\n- screenplay global validation failures -> retry affected batches when possible\n- semantic polish failures -> retry affected polish batches when possible\n- scene_bible builder failures -> retry builder step\n- retry limit -> abort\n\n## Parallelism policy (initial)\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n## Parallelism rules\n- parallelize only batchable operators\n- keep validators, mergers, builders, schema validation, checkpointing, and preflight sequential\n- do not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- preserve selective retry rather than rerunning everything by default\n\n## Escalation rule\nIf retries are exhausted or structural issues persist, fail clearly and escalate upward rather than improvising hidden recovery.\n\n## Acceptance rule\nCanonical artifacts should only be advanced when the supervisor has enough validation basis to accept them.\nRejected or unvalidated operator outputs must not be treated as sector truth.\n\nFor the screenplay lane specifically:\n- batch success alone is not enough\n- the merged screenplay becomes materially accepted only after `screenplay_validator` approval\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775114518873}}
{"type":"message","id":"7de83f19","parentId":"7ea978f9","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:21:59.023Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_apCLp9ZpLecxSHdR9ZP5LEPk|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce1917255c8190b53716821f581192","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical sector flow\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build `scene_director` payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule `scene_director` batches with controlled parallelism via `operator_batch_scheduler`\n6. Invoke `scene_director` batches under supervisor control\n7. Reconstruct/canonicalize `scene_director` batch mechanics deterministically when needed\n8. Validate each batch via `scene_director_output_validator`\n9. If needed, classify retry via `retry_planner`\n10. Merge approved/canonicalized scene batches via `screenplay_merger`\n11. Validate canonical screenplay via `screenplay_validator`\n12. If screenplay validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n12. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n13. Build `tts_polish` payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n14. Schedule `tts_polish` batches with controlled parallelism via `operator_batch_scheduler`\n15. Invoke `tts_polish` batches under supervisor control\n16. Validate each polish batch via `tts_polish_output_validator`\n17. Route only ambiguous cases to `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` when needed\n18. Merge approved polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n19. Validate canonical polish via `polish_validator`\n20. If polish validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n21. Build `scene_bible.json` via `scene_bible_builder`\n22. Validate scene bible schema via `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n23. Write/check checkpoints via `checkpoint_writer`\n24. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n25. Complete or fail the sector\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\n- Use selective retry when possible\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n- Do not allow unvalidated batch outputs into canonical merge artifacts\n- The supervisor remains the owner of sequencing and acceptance decisions\n- Semantic review is a narrow escalation lane, not a default second pass for all polish batches\n- The `scene_director` lane is hybrid: semantic grouping belongs primarily to the operator, while exact span/alignment mechanics may be reconstructed/canonicalized by deterministic substrate\n- If the semantic output is still useful, prefer deterministic recovery before discarding the batch\n- Localized boundary problems should be treated as repair candidates when possible, not immediate proof that the whole sector design is wrong\n- A merged screenplay is only materially accepted when the whole-artifact validator approves it\n\n## Important current implementation note\n`operator_batch_scheduler` currently plans waves and summarizes execution.\nIt does **not** itself invoke OpenClaw operators.\nThe supervisor must still own the actual operator invocation/control loop.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775114518955}}
{"type":"message","id":"087de7fc","parentId":"7de83f19","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:21:59.091Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_w8jFcn38AW0o4YKHgUwclrIY|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce191725648190b68031396996f701","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector\nS1 / B1 — Pre-Production\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar o script bruto persistido pelo VO numa base narrativa estruturada pronta para o resto da pipeline.\n\n## Canonical runtime rule\nO runtime canónico do setor é o próprio `sm_s1_pre_production`.\n\nO supervisor é a autoridade de runtime do S1 para:\n- sequencing\n- invocation decisions\n- validation interpretation\n- retry / fail / continue / escalate\n- sector completion\n\nQualquer camada Python auxiliar deve ser tratada como bootstrap/transição, não como soberania do setor.\n\n## Input assumptions\nA run que entra no S1 deve ter pelo menos:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar, o setor deve deixar:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n## Current proven milestone\nO lane de screenplay já foi provado numa run controlada real `PM -> VO -> S1`:\n- `b1_step1_screenplay` concluído\n- `b1_step2_screenplay_validated` concluído\n- `screenplay_validator` aprovou o artefacto com coverage total\n\nIsto desloca a principal zona de incerteza para o que acontece **depois** do screenplay, não para o `scene_director` em si.\n\n## Component classes in the sector\n### Supervisor\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\n\n### Semantic operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n### Supervisor deterministic skills\n- preflight\n- paths resolution\n- batching\n- operator I/O bridge\n- per-batch structural validation\n- merge\n- retry planning\n- controlled scheduling\n- result summarization\n\n### Shared deterministic components\n- whole-screenplay validation\n- whole-polish validation\n- scene bible build\n- scene bible schema validation\n- checkpoint writing\n\n## Naming convention\nCanonical naming is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*`\n\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical.\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: VO (`ready_for_s1`)\n- Next layers: S2 and S3 (`ready_for_s2_and_s3`)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775114519027}}
{"type":"message","id":"1215cca0","parentId":"087de7fc","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:22:06.824Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating session issues**\n\nI’m noticing a contradiction with the current run, possibly due to an old run versus the latest one. I think I need to inspect the agent session to pinpoint any failures. It might help to check the sessions list as well. However, the task is asking for the highest-leverage fix, so I need to locate the code repository. I might search through the user directory with a command to check common directories.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce191ba79c819099e4311e91627e5e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpzhkfljLJ6MyEsXjf2lyaXl08wDUPhzKaFyQeCXQRouwfHmVOtENCi35a2zL__FVySX2nkN9TEZCAVUQmIT1YLgsGTqqUr3jVB8GLIWLaDJ_AxjnXcXeHeZUbhCs_DxucJT82bEZz3-Uxw20ku81-KLkTemLVRpRRekKopg3XRncArqNPH22_Gmf9rPMhfiLPyy_XknR759uHIZykgsvaMSlwTpz-5saQAXc6aQYrrkJ8UIQTakHUraw9UIgON88bbsMWDIwnXiL5VDo0RD7lXppNsb73Wlxz34HrJLvxuwfh_jknlqvxLlAxD8GhAnwX7doR80K6P5I1IR8NsVXhU4FZGpPtbu1VhQHb7-6kRqcabuOrC0g5LgW9M_W5gE3q9QwVFAN1QSk1IJp9bAF9MLhDIMDo9_GrKv7rGLTGKSGkn1xFvGcFVc0cvJyWvQuoJGWZiM_HEnQwVwzEkIclQd3nPfmPefyj7T9nI8FiIOM4EcLPMvDLYY2SSXXYBVQUQketIFdvempfwDNd7ZMbeY5kzKj0jX-0YiRR56GesrknaXlsZTIrFkXxKL1h27mt_rCk-8WsKitld3-NRJ1887_7nhXYFv60kBfO7sXD5Ozw43Uq00nOUWcOYan9ZMwYZXH48cv7foTo_RJPX40Kh0n2dqPAw90PzpZKTwvGfxqR3iblD6Pd2LwlXt9zeGU4I8hepv_TGkOpatVSBAJsDqWY7kU9ACFzaC0XHelnA_3p1QNpHdxR8c4CkpvvtesXaqDj2Pp2rFUcVlXa7lF5bq2ncjawMCIIMVr_-j4-4aza9jiaesTabIexyoXB7n-PCSL6Y22Ot2lLMnEwYPkq_3H-JFZKgm1fzDOgRNjoPvkqN9cL0oXEIw-bfjA8OVPbHE30IH6M6M7JkuUQbKnFgxLj0ogDsfuhip_AYMzvCpuSr52DWG6-0gFrsP6iZt7lbMwf7YEHw-iU-YiFzwIHn03HT25k6_TthUiUHLtBUuehunJBjNwoQJnQMRLCwUF6DNjdYSS9sUvYVmb1Lq3wPgb1JN-a7E6657NfD3ncjSxiLpmX77m86RcOwH1swx0PWuESVQH71Q6o1Hw7bGsVEh4Bq8K0xI9k-HbaMhV9zTPBbtw15OWhPMo2kK84g-mmluhtG49vTIPHjPQ5eci2IkImlmC73h_y6qULPLh2BOE3Lbb1e8tCTD0ojSFK2T3zEpYBaSdiyiN_c5dkmvZjgivSz82rDvIG