ry_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating fallback options**\\n\\nFor the failed ones, I’m thinking about salvaging the process by loading the payload and possibly using existing output while preserving unchanged scenes if the validator is okay. That seems complicated per scene. If there are validation errors, it might be simpler to rewrite the batch using payload scenes and adjust things like `narration_tts = narration_original`. This approach could pass the validator and serve as a solid fallback. Maybe adding a warning code would help, too. Let’s patch this!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Vou aplicar um fallback determinístico no lane de `tts_polish`: quando o worker sair inválido ou semanticamente suspeito, o supervisor reescreve o batch de forma segura com `narration_tts = narration_original` em vez de falhar o run todo. Սա aumenta robustez imediatamente e testa a viabilidade real do caminho OpenClaw com substrate protector.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce1a011ca0819087881d37b3b52176\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_oMmOYkicI71lPxlTmuNWdtRG|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce1a013fe0819084f0d170fa7c8a9b","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_runtime.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    approved_batch_files: list[str] = []\n    failed_batch_ids: list[str] = []\n    localized_meaning_flags = 0\n    for batch in prepared_batches:\n        validation = validate_tts_polish_output(\n            batch_payload_path=batch[\"input_path\"],\n            batch_output_path=batch[\"output_path\"],\n        )\n        validation_errors = validation.get(\"errors\", [])\n        meaning_only = validation_errors and all(err.get(\"code\") == \"meaningful_change_detected\" for err in validation_errors)\n        localized_flag_count = sum(1 for err in validation_errors if err.get(\"code\") == \"meaningful_change_detected\")\n\n        if validation.get(\"approved_for_merge\") or (meaning_only and localized_flag_count <= 4):\n            approved_batch_files.append(batch[\"output_path\"])\n            if meaning_only and localized_flag_count <= 4:\n                localized_meaning_flags += localized_flag_count\n                warnings.append(\n                    {\n                        \"code\": \"localized_meaningful_change_tolerated\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Accepted batch {batch['batch_id']} with {localized_flag_count} localized meaningful_change_detected flags.\",\n                    }\n                )\n            continue\n\n        failed_batch_ids.append(batch[\"batch_id\"])\n        errors.extend(validation_errors)\n","newText":"    approved_batch_files: list[str] = []\n    failed_batch_ids: list[str] = []\n    localized_meaning_flags = 0\n    for batch in prepared_batches:\n        validation = validate_tts_polish_output(\n            batch_payload_path=batch[\"input_path\"],\n            batch_output_path=batch[\"output_path\"],\n        )\n        validation_errors = validation.get(\"errors\", [])\n        meaning_only = validation_errors and all(err.get(\"code\") == \"meaningful_change_detected\" for err in validation_errors)\n        localized_flag_count = sum(1 for err in validation_errors if err.get(\"code\") == \"meaningful_change_detected\")\n\n        if validation.get(\"approved_for_merge\") or (meaning_only and localized_flag_count <= 4):\n            approved_batch_files.append(batch[\"output_path\"])\n            if meaning_only and localized_flag_count <= 4:\n                localized_meaning_flags += localized_flag_count\n                warnings.append(\n                    {\n                        \"code\": \"localized_meaningful_change_tolerated\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Accepted batch {batch['batch_id']} with {localized_flag_count} localized meaningful_change_detected flags.\",\n                    }\n                )\n            continue\n\n        fallback_result = _rewrite_tts_polish_batch_as_identity(\n            batch_payload_path=batch[\"input_path\"],\n            batch_output_path=batch[\"output_path\"],\n            reason_codes=[err.get(\"code\", \"unknown_error\") for err in validation_errors],\n        )\n        warnings.extend(fallback_result.get(\"warnings\", []))\n        if fallback_result.get(\"ok\"):\n            fallback_validation = validate_tts_polish_output(\n                batch_payload_path=batch[\"input_path\"],\n                batch_output_path=batch[\"output_path\"],\n            )\n            if fallback_validation.get(\"approved_for_merge\"):\n                approved_batch_files.append(batch[\"output_path\"])\n                continue\n            validation_errors = fallback_validation.get(\"errors\", validation_errors)\n\n        failed_batch_ids.append(batch[\"batch_id\"])\n        errors.extend(validation_errors)\n"},{"oldText":"def _build_scene_director_agent_message(input_path: str, output_path: str) -> str:\n","newText":"def _rewrite_tts_polish_batch_as_identity(\n    *,\n    batch_payload_path: str | Path,\n    batch_output_path: str | Path,\n    reason_codes: list[str] | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    payload_path = Path(batch_payload_path)\n    output_path = Path(batch_output_path)\n\n    try:\n        payload = json.loads(payload_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"warnings\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"tts_polish_identity_fallback_payload_unreadable\", \"message\": f\"Failed to read payload for deterministic fallback: {exc}\"}],\n        }\n\n    batch = payload.get(\"batch\", {}) if isinstance(payload, dict) else {}\n    scenes = payload.get(\"scenes\", []) if isinstance(payload, dict) else []\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list) or not scenes:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"warnings\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"tts_polish_identity_fallback_invalid_payload\", \"message\": \"Cannot build deterministic fallback without payload scenes.\"}],\n        }\n\n    fallback_output = {\n        \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\") or output_path.stem.replace(\"_output\", \"\"),\n        \"operator\": \"tts_polish_identity_fallback\",\n        \"scenes\": [],\n    }\n\n    for scene in scenes:\n        if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n            continue\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n        narration_original = scene.get(\"narration_original\")\n        if not isinstance(scene_id, str) or not isinstance(narration_original, str):\n            continue\n        fallback_output[\"scenes\"].append(\n            {\n                \"scene_id\": scene_id,\n                \"narration_original\": narration_original,\n                \"narration_tts\": narration_original,\n                \"changes\": [],\n            }\n        )\n\n    if not fallback_output[\"scenes\"]:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"warnings\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"tts_polish_identity_fallback_empty\", \"message\": \"Deterministic fallback produced zero scenes.\"}],\n        }\n\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    output_path.write_text(json.dumps(fallback_output, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"warnings\": [\n            {\n                \"code\": \"tts_polish_identity_fallback_applied\",\n                \"message\": (\n                    f\"Applied deterministic identity fallback for {fallback_output['batch_id']} \"\n                    f\"after validation errors: {sorted(set(reason_codes or []))}\"\n                ),\n            }\n        ],\n        \"errors\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef _build_scene_director_agent_message(input_path: str, output_path: str) -> str:\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desk