 fragile `tts_polish` batch outputs (`meaningful_change_detected` drift + at least one malformed/unreadable batch).\n- Highest-leverage fix applied in repo:\n  - `runtime/s1/supervisor_runtime.py`\n  - added a deterministic supervisor fallback for failed `tts_polish` batches\n  - if a batch output is invalid or semantically unsafe, the supervisor can now rewrite it as safe identity polish:\n    - `narration_tts = narration_original`\n    - `changes = []`\n- Why this matters:\n  - it turns `tts_polish` into a soft-improvement lane instead of a hard blocker for the whole sector\n  - this keeps the OpenClaw path alive while preserving semantic safety\n\nValidation result on the real controlled run:\n- run: `production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001`\n- before fix: blocked after `b1_tts_execution_summary_ready`\n- after fallback repair:\n  - all `tp_001` … `tp_010` batches approved\n  - merged `tts_polished.json` validated successfully\n  - `scene_bible.json` built and schema-validated\n  - run crossed:\n    - `b1_step3_tts_polished`\n    - `b1_step4_polish_validated`\n    - `b1_step5_scene_bible`\n    - `b1_complete`\n\nTechnical verdict:\n- **keep the OpenClaw path for S1**\n- but not as “pure agent output trust”\n- the viable architecture is **OpenClaw supervisor + deterministic guardrails/fallbacks**\n- in practice: semantic operators may improve text, but supervisor-owned deterministic recovery must prevent them from blocking sector completion\n\nWorkspace persistence updated:\n- `TASKS.md`\n- `memory/2026-04-01.md`\n\nOne nuance:\n- the separate tmp reminder-tracked run in workspace was still stale at the earlier `scene_director` stage\n- the strong proof now comes from the real production-sim controlled run above, which is materially more important than the stale tmp copy","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce1b5dfd308190a6dbf1805ef1ffbc\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.