can rewrite it as identity polish:\n  - `narration_tts = narration_original`\n  - `changes = []`\n\n3. **Real validation result**\n- Validated against the real controlled run:\n  - `production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001`\n- After fallback repair:\n  - all `tp_###` batches approved\n  - `tts_polished.json` validated\n  - `scene_bible.json` built + schema-valid\n  - run crossed:\n    - `b1_step3_tts_polished`\n    - `b1_step4_polish_validated`\n    - `b1_step5_scene_bible`\n    - `b1_complete`\n\n4. **Important nuance**\n- The separate tmp monitored run in workspace (`tmp_pm_vo_s1_real/.../2026-04-01_003_fr_001`) is still stale/stalled before `b1_step1_screenplay`.\n- That tmp run should not be mistaken for the strongest evidence.\n- The real proof now comes from the production-sim run above.\n\n5. **Persistence updated**\n- `TASKS.md` updated\n- `memory/2026-04-01.md` updated\n\nBottom line:\n- The night did produce a serious result, not just “tested again.”\n- S1 now has a technically grounded **keep** verdict, with a concrete robustness pattern:\n  **semantic lane optional, deterministic safety mandatory.**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce29a19c8c81908883f58f67df567b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":136648,"output":476,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139684,"cost":{"input":0.34162000000000003,"output":0.0071400000000000005,"cacheRead":0.0006399999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.3494}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775118746163,"responseId":"resp_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce299c18bc8190adebc20b5adda48c"}}
