\":\"**Evaluating response options**\\n\\nI think I need to respond with a concise summary here. The instruction suggests I should read the current context and utilize recent memory. Should I use memory_search for prior information? It seems logical. I might also mention the current run state from brisk-willow or if it's stalled. I don't have to poll loops, but it’s okay to retrieve information on-demand. I'll keep it focused on what’s needed.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Qp0UFMgxRY7bBBaogeORyMBZ|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce37eaa8dc8190bd6ef84d2df4cf26","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"S1 overnight supervision current run brisk-willow materialization latest conclusions keep redesign abort latest failures","maxResults":6},"partialJson":"{\"query\":\"S1 overnight supervision current run brisk-willow materialization latest conclusions keep redesign abort latest failures\",\"maxResults\":6}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_vurYzXkdWf4tz0p5D1ktGKab|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce37eaa8f08190aaaf342ca9cdf38a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"TASKS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"TASKS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_gmkCtXvYTEwFhF4pcowX9K1X|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce37eaa8f881908f096f74045a21d3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"memory/2026-04-01.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"memory/2026-04-01.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ZGfNwZUjxkZhlYjQMDvaKGcI|fc_0408171ee7a64bae0169ce37eaa900819095cc55b3eb4d6dec","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"log","sessionId":"brisk-willow","offset":0,"limit":200},"partialJson":"{\"action\":\"log\",\"sessionId\":\"brisk-willow\",\"offset\":0,\"limit\":200}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":148078,"output":179,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148257,"cost":{"input":0.37019500000000005,"output":0.002685,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.37288000000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775122397006,"responseId":"resp_0408171ee7a64bae0