oved trust instead of behaving like allow-once</strong>, reuse exact-command trust on shell-wrapper paths that cannot safely persist an executable allowlist entry, keep static allowlist entries ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4bbbb8cb42d9d890\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7ff87a64b1dfc061\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nopenclaw/openclaw v2026.4.1-beta.1 on GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7ff87a64b1dfc061\">>>","url":"https://newreleases.io/project/github/openclaw/openclaw/release/v2026.4.1-beta.1","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ee1af0737ed4f9f8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nExec/approvals: <strong>make allow-always persist as durable user-approved trust instead of behaving like allow-once</strong>, reuse exact-command trust on shell-wrapper paths that cannot safely persist an executable allowlist entry, keep static allowlist entries ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ee1af0737ed4f9f8\">>>","published":"1 day ago","siteName":"newreleases.io"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b116482ebaea8e54\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n`allow-always` exec approvals on nodes don't take effect until gateway restart · Issue #46573 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b116482ebaea8e54\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/46573","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4ebb3c009cc69ac3\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nWhen a user clicks &quot;Always allow&quot; on an exec approval prompt for a host=node command, the allowlist entry is persisted to the node&#x27;s ~/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json, but the gateway continues prompting because it reads its own local file instead of querying the node&#x27;s allowlist.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4ebb3c009cc69ac3\">>>","published":"3 weeks ago","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"20433ff603f1f6ff\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\